00:05:01.220 --> 00:05:03.060
- Well I'm here as tonight's philosopher,

00:05:03.060 --> 00:05:04.811
but also tonight's lawyer.

00:05:04.811 --> 00:05:08.490
Philosophers are interested
in lots of forms of freedom:

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:10.309
freedom in the sense
of freedom of the will,

00:05:10.309 --> 00:05:14.240
freedom from unmet
material needs and wants,

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:17.080
freedom from unjust constraint, coercion,

00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:19.440
harassment and other kinds of domination

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:21.360
by people and organizations,

00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:24.260
and freedom in the sense of
having a range of opportunities

00:05:24.260 --> 00:05:26.240
to develop, exercise, and display

00:05:26.240 --> 00:05:29.810
one's individual abilities,
character, and moral judgment,

00:05:29.810 --> 00:05:32.310
and conditions of mutual
respect among others,

00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:34.760
including the opportunities for fulfilling

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:38.000
work and leisure, for equal
political participation,

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:41.520
and for supporting, loving,
and chosen relationships.

00:05:41.520 --> 00:05:44.950
These are all vital forms
of freedom and, indeed,

00:05:44.950 --> 00:05:48.610
the quest of some UC workers
for these very forms of freedom

00:05:48.610 --> 00:05:52.910
is indirectly why we're here
tonight at this location.

00:05:52.910 --> 00:05:54.670
But the direct reason we're here tonight

00:05:54.670 --> 00:05:57.240
is not their cause, but their protest

00:05:57.240 --> 00:05:59.430
through the exercise of freedom of speech,

00:05:59.430 --> 00:06:01.260
and that's my topic.

00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:03.890
I wanna take my time to
discuss the relationship

00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:06.590
between freedom of speech
and freedom of thought,

00:06:06.590 --> 00:06:09.130
and how their legal
and cultural protection

00:06:09.130 --> 00:06:11.110
underpins the freedom to live a life

00:06:11.110 --> 00:06:13.480
of meaning and authenticity.

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:15.972
My claim is that freedom of speech

00:06:15.972 --> 00:06:18.700
is critical to freedom of thought,

00:06:18.700 --> 00:06:21.020
and in turn both freedom of thought

00:06:21.020 --> 00:06:23.180
and freedom of speech are essential

00:06:23.180 --> 00:06:26.180
for meaningful thoughts,
meaningful speech,

00:06:26.180 --> 00:06:29.770
conscientious and authentic
self-representation,

00:06:29.770 --> 00:06:32.763
and ultimately meaningful
relationships with others.

00:06:33.940 --> 00:06:37.650
I'm gonna take as my starting
point a landmark legal case

00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:41.000
involving the Constitutional
right not to speak:

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.293
West Virginia Board of
Education v. Barnette.

00:06:44.450 --> 00:06:48.010
In 1943 the Supreme Court recognized

00:06:48.010 --> 00:06:50.165
that students have a First Amendment right

00:06:50.165 --> 00:06:53.590
to choose not to recite
the Pledge of Allegiance,

00:06:53.590 --> 00:06:55.130
and so I ask you all to join me

00:06:55.130 --> 00:06:57.300
in exercising your right to decide

00:06:57.300 --> 00:06:59.285
whether to recite the
Pledge of Allegiance.

00:06:59.285 --> 00:07:01.410
I hope you'll decide right now not to,

00:07:01.410 --> 00:07:06.410
but I was asked to think
about audience participation,

00:07:06.620 --> 00:07:08.060
and that's the best I could do.

00:07:08.060 --> 00:07:09.300
(laughs)
I'm sure the others

00:07:09.300 --> 00:07:10.413
will be better at it.

00:07:11.400 --> 00:07:14.220
But back to Barnette, the
litigants in that case

00:07:14.220 --> 00:07:16.900
were a really brave family
of Jehovah's Witnesses

00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:18.820
who objected to reciting the pledge

00:07:18.820 --> 00:07:20.180
given their religious commitment

00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:21.873
not to worship false idols.

00:07:23.062 --> 00:07:26.980
The case happened after a
summer of very intense violence

00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:28.970
against the country's Jehovah's Witnesses

00:07:28.970 --> 00:07:31.660
for their stance on the flag,

00:07:31.660 --> 00:07:33.530
and the Barnette court held

00:07:33.530 --> 00:07:35.280
that compelling children to recite

00:07:35.280 --> 00:07:37.760
the Pledge of Allegiance
violated the First Amendment's

00:07:37.760 --> 00:07:39.500
free speech guarantee.

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:41.300
In its most stirring passage,

00:07:41.300 --> 00:07:44.217
Justice Jackson's majority
opinion proclaimed,

00:07:44.217 --> 00:07:46.147
"If there's any fixed star

00:07:46.147 --> 00:07:48.697
"in our constitutional constellation,

00:07:48.697 --> 00:07:51.097
"it's that no official high or petty

00:07:51.097 --> 00:07:54.517
"can prescribe what shall
be orthodox in politics,

00:07:54.517 --> 00:07:58.077
"nationalism, religion, or
other matters of opinion,

00:07:58.077 --> 00:08:00.707
"or force citizens to confess by word

00:08:00.707 --> 00:08:03.470
"or act their faith therein."

00:08:03.470 --> 00:08:07.320
During that fraught time
full of anxiety and fear

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:09.140
on the brink of World War II,

00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:11.620
the Barnette court took an important stand

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:13.840
to respect religious minorities

00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:17.330
and to protect nonconformist expression.

00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:21.490
This year we celebrate that
case's 75th anniversary.

00:08:21.490 --> 00:08:25.548
But the controversy over
Colin Kaepernick and his view

00:08:25.548 --> 00:08:28.140
shows that the wisdom of that decision

00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:30.280
has not been fully absorbed in the culture

00:08:30.280 --> 00:08:32.133
and, hence, it's worth returning to.

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:35.350
You might wonder why
this freedom of speech

00:08:35.350 --> 00:08:37.380
demanded the right to remain silent,

00:08:37.380 --> 00:08:39.760
after all isn't all that's important

00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:42.360
is that one has the freedom
to say what one thinks

00:08:42.360 --> 00:08:44.740
and to have one's views understood?

00:08:44.740 --> 00:08:47.640
No one takes a compelled
recitation to reflect

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:49.740
the speaker's deepest thoughts.

00:08:49.740 --> 00:08:52.100
It's socially understood
that it's a ritual

00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:53.260
to promote unity,

00:08:53.260 --> 00:08:56.520
not to express an
individual's true thinking.

00:08:56.520 --> 00:08:59.200
So long as one can criticize the Pledge

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:03.160
and its presuppositions before
and after its recitation,

00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:05.260
why would freedom of speech guarantee

00:09:05.260 --> 00:09:07.030
the freedom to exempt oneself

00:09:07.030 --> 00:09:10.550
from unifying community
activities that no one thinks of

00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:13.200
as my speech or your speech?

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:16.340
I'm gonna offer three reasons
why we should think that.

00:09:16.340 --> 00:09:18.530
First, the dignity of individuals

00:09:18.530 --> 00:09:20.370
and their interest in freedom of thought

00:09:20.370 --> 00:09:23.587
precludes the State's attempting
to influence their minds

00:09:23.587 --> 00:09:25.860
by recruiting their speech facility

00:09:25.860 --> 00:09:29.960
through compelled and
scripted routine recitation.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:32.290
Ritual affirmations can influence

00:09:32.290 --> 00:09:35.240
a person's thought in an insidious way.

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:37.560
Rather than through direct persuasion,

00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:40.270
regular compelled speech can bypass

00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:42.320
a person's rational deliberation

00:09:42.320 --> 00:09:45.440
and recruit her instincts
associated with virtues

00:09:45.440 --> 00:09:48.900
of sincerity and the
phenomenon of familiarity

00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:51.860
to identify and then
absorb as one's thought

00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:53.260
what one has said.

00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:55.410
You might start reflexively thinking

00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:57.660
that this is in fact a nation under God

00:09:57.660 --> 00:09:59.450
despite the First Amendment's guarantee

00:09:59.450 --> 00:10:00.890
of freedom of religion,

00:10:00.890 --> 00:10:03.293
including the freedom to be an Atheist.

00:10:03.293 --> 00:10:05.930
Given the natural feel of a phrase

00:10:05.930 --> 00:10:08.760
after frequent repetition of its rhythm,

00:10:08.760 --> 00:10:10.940
one might start to hear it in one's head

00:10:10.940 --> 00:10:14.190
in one's own voice and start
to instinctively think,

00:10:14.190 --> 00:10:17.180
well this is a land with
liberty and justice for all,

00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:19.840
whether the evidence
supports that aspiration

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:21.133
or contradicts it.

00:10:22.010 --> 00:10:25.940
Second, by hijacking a person's
speech against her will

00:10:25.940 --> 00:10:29.260
the State involves a
person in insincerity.

00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:32.470
This puts her speech in tension
with her moral integrity

00:10:32.470 --> 00:10:33.960
and her independence,

00:10:33.960 --> 00:10:36.900
and that's an untenable
dilemma for a person,

00:10:36.900 --> 00:10:39.410
and it's a self-destructive
stance for a polity

00:10:39.410 --> 00:10:43.093
that depends on a responsible
and free-minded citizenry.

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:47.530
Now, of course it's true that
healthy social cooperation

00:10:47.530 --> 00:10:51.007
requires cooperating sometimes
in ways we wouldn't choose,

00:10:51.007 --> 00:10:55.650
but what makes that compromise
tolerable for all of us

00:10:55.650 --> 00:10:59.120
is that we still retain our
distinct judgment, identity,

00:10:59.120 --> 00:11:01.960
and opinions, and we can question whether

00:11:01.960 --> 00:11:05.510
we together should
continue that cooperation.

00:11:05.510 --> 00:11:08.640
But when the State demands
that we affirm or attest

00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:10.800
to things that we worry are false,

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:14.471
we've moved beyond that compromise
in the face of difference

00:11:14.471 --> 00:11:17.020
to a state of domination,

00:11:17.020 --> 00:11:19.890
a disrespectful attempt at homogenization

00:11:19.890 --> 00:11:23.050
and a denigration of the
ongoing critical judgment

00:11:23.050 --> 00:11:27.340
that's necessary for progress
and for democratic legitimacy.

00:11:27.340 --> 00:11:29.970
Neither the State nor
the culture should ask us

00:11:29.970 --> 00:11:31.963
to face that untenable dilemma.

00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:36.850
Third, compelled recitations
deprive recitations

00:11:36.850 --> 00:11:37.920
of much meaning;

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:40.460
they become coerced and empty rituals,

00:11:40.460 --> 00:11:42.790
not true affirmations.

00:11:42.790 --> 00:11:45.350
But by contrast, the freedom not to speak

00:11:45.350 --> 00:11:46.850
not only serves the integrity

00:11:46.850 --> 00:11:50.930
of the thought of the person
who chooses not to speak,

00:11:50.930 --> 00:11:52.550
it also renders the speech

00:11:52.550 --> 00:11:56.270
of those who continue to
participate more meaningful.

00:11:56.270 --> 00:11:58.310
When there's a clear option not to speak,

00:11:58.310 --> 00:12:01.890
and especially when some
people like the Barnettes,

00:12:01.890 --> 00:12:04.730
like Colin Kaepernick pave the way,

00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:06.990
that live option now prods you

00:12:06.990 --> 00:12:08.910
to think about what those words mean

00:12:08.910 --> 00:12:12.040
and why some demure from affirming them,

00:12:12.040 --> 00:12:15.070
and that option creates
pressure for your choice

00:12:15.070 --> 00:12:17.160
to say then to be deliberate

00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:18.490
rather than to be robotic,

00:12:18.490 --> 00:12:22.810
and thus to reflect a true
endorsement of what you say.

00:12:22.810 --> 00:12:26.190
Thus the silence of some
has the power to transform

00:12:26.190 --> 00:12:28.750
the speech of others from a rote ritual

00:12:28.750 --> 00:12:32.090
into a more meaningful and
thoughtful affirmation;

00:12:32.090 --> 00:12:36.427
thereby, paying deeper tribute
to the values one espouses.

00:12:36.427 --> 00:12:40.090
There's a parallel point that
should be familiar in art,

00:12:40.090 --> 00:12:43.300
whether from the use of
negative space in visual art

00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.590
or as I've learned from
my favorite pianist,

00:12:45.590 --> 00:12:49.840
Pierre-Laurent Aimard, the
modernist use of acoustic silence

00:12:49.840 --> 00:12:51.850
to give greater resonance to the notes

00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:55.770
when they are later struck and
the phrases that they form,

00:12:55.770 --> 00:12:58.470
and maybe the absence
of my picture on screen

00:12:58.470 --> 00:13:02.350
makes my words a little more potent.

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:06.130
This enablement of nuanced
and meaningful communication

00:13:06.130 --> 00:13:08.210
is important for individuals to be able

00:13:08.210 --> 00:13:11.950
to represent themselves
as distinct thinkers

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:14.240
and to be known for who they are.

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:16.670
It's vitally significant for achieving

00:13:16.670 --> 00:13:18.550
and maintaining self-respect

00:13:18.550 --> 00:13:20.803
and a sense of the respect of others.

00:13:22.310 --> 00:13:25.677
One way that the State enables
such meaningful communication

00:13:25.677 --> 00:13:29.430
is when it refrains from
demanding compelled affirmations,

00:13:29.430 --> 00:13:31.550
but also when it protects dissonance

00:13:31.550 --> 00:13:33.481
and encourages critical discourse,

00:13:33.481 --> 00:13:35.699
when it funds substantive education

00:13:35.699 --> 00:13:38.390
as at the University of California,

00:13:38.390 --> 00:13:40.840
and also when it passes legislation,

00:13:40.840 --> 00:13:44.379
like the California Gender
Recognition Act of 2017,

00:13:44.379 --> 00:13:48.866
SB-179, which enables people
without medical documentation

00:13:48.866 --> 00:13:52.210
to select male, female, or non-binary

00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:54.070
on their driver's licenses and IDs

00:13:54.070 --> 00:13:57.440
so that they can gain
recognition officially

00:13:57.440 --> 00:13:59.790
of their own self-identification.

00:13:59.790 --> 00:14:03.373
This act heightens my
pride to be a Californian.

00:14:04.620 --> 00:14:08.360
So I was discussing how
enabling the freedom to engage

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:11.080
in conscientious, vocalized departures

00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:14.780
from standardized sentiments,
routines, rituals,

00:14:14.780 --> 00:14:18.220
and classifications
enable all of us together

00:14:18.220 --> 00:14:21.600
as individuals to engage
in more meaningful speech.

00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:23.482
These opportunities for greater meaning

00:14:23.482 --> 00:14:27.220
in turn facilitate deeper
human relationships

00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:30.080
that are more responsive
to what we actually think,

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:31.950
rather than what we're presumed to think

00:14:31.950 --> 00:14:33.840
or expected to think.

00:14:33.840 --> 00:14:36.317
But for that freedom to
achieve its potential,

00:14:36.317 --> 00:14:39.200
all of us have to listen to each other,

00:14:39.200 --> 00:14:42.270
and that point returns
me to why we are all

00:14:42.270 --> 00:14:44.236
north of Sunset tonight.

00:14:44.236 --> 00:14:48.180
The very idea that principled disruptions

00:14:48.180 --> 00:14:50.380
from standardized routines can provoke

00:14:50.380 --> 00:14:53.341
greater thoughtfulness and
engagement with important values

00:14:53.341 --> 00:14:56.790
is literally why we're here in this gym.

00:14:56.790 --> 00:14:59.200
We're here and not in Kaufman

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:01.217
because university healthcare workers,

00:15:01.217 --> 00:15:05.150
supported by their fellow
custodians, are on strike,

00:15:05.150 --> 00:15:08.560
and a strike, after all,
is a principled departure

00:15:08.560 --> 00:15:11.890
from a standardized routine
that aims to communicate

00:15:11.890 --> 00:15:14.380
in a peaceful but forceful way

00:15:14.380 --> 00:15:17.080
that the workers feel they're
not being listened to.

00:15:17.080 --> 00:15:19.290
It's not a whimsical decision they make.

00:15:19.290 --> 00:15:22.280
It's a collectively
made, democratic decision

00:15:22.280 --> 00:15:25.240
by the relatively vulnerable and poor

00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:28.920
to go without pay to send the message

00:15:28.920 --> 00:15:31.359
that they perceive things as bad enough

00:15:31.359 --> 00:15:34.950
that business as usual is inappropriate.

00:15:34.950 --> 00:15:38.680
They're willing to absorb
three days of the lack of pay,

00:15:38.680 --> 00:15:42.000
three days of cost, to send this message,

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:44.330
and they ask us to do that too

00:15:44.330 --> 00:15:47.030
to prompt other people to listen.

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:49.010
By respecting their picket line

00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:51.840
we show that we register
how strongly they feel

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:55.353
their concerns and their
profound sense of neglect.

00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:59.000
That's not the same as
agreeing with their claims

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:01.700
that they're shouldering
an unfair proportion

00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:03.660
of the burdens associated with providing

00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:05.560
the material conditions that enable

00:16:05.560 --> 00:16:08.150
all of our intellectual freedom.

00:16:08.150 --> 00:16:10.180
But it's rather to acknowledge

00:16:10.180 --> 00:16:12.033
that the issues deserve attention.

00:16:12.890 --> 00:16:15.720
So I hope this experience inspires you

00:16:15.720 --> 00:16:17.600
to investigate their concerns,

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:19.090
to learn about their concerns,

00:16:19.090 --> 00:16:21.740
and to learn about the
university's position.

00:16:21.740 --> 00:16:25.790
More generally, I urge you to
commit to take full advantage

00:16:25.790 --> 00:16:29.290
and full responsibility for
your intellectual freedom,

00:16:29.290 --> 00:16:33.010
because exploratory, deliberate speech

00:16:33.010 --> 00:16:36.030
and deliberate silence
and engaged listening

00:16:36.030 --> 00:16:38.160
and dialogue are the central pillars

00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:41.428
of a free and meaningful life.

00:16:41.428 --> 00:16:45.511
(audience applauds)
- Everybody.

00:16:48.530 --> 00:16:50.996
Everybody, Seanna Valentine Shiffrin.

00:16:50.996 --> 00:16:52.410
Thank you so much, Seanna.

00:16:52.410 --> 00:16:54.390
Our next presentation this evening

00:16:54.390 --> 00:16:55.863
