00:17:08.290 --> 00:17:10.313
So I am going to address freedom

00:17:10.313 --> 00:17:15.230
in the context of our ability to act

00:17:15.230 --> 00:17:18.460
with freewill without
constraint within the systems

00:17:18.460 --> 00:17:20.670
of control that we build around ourselves,

00:17:20.670 --> 00:17:24.240
the social ones as well
as the technological ones.

00:17:24.240 --> 00:17:26.150
I'll present a few attempts

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:29.430
to render some of these systems visible

00:17:29.430 --> 00:17:31.420
and to hold space within them to find

00:17:31.420 --> 00:17:34.020
both more nuanced understandings of them

00:17:34.020 --> 00:17:36.470
and relationships within them.

00:17:36.470 --> 00:17:40.530
So in 2013 I was looking
closely at two of these systems:

00:17:40.530 --> 00:17:42.630
the first one online dating,

00:17:42.630 --> 00:17:44.439
which you're probably familiar with,

00:17:44.439 --> 00:17:47.460
and the second, Amazon Mechanical Turk.

00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:49.760
So if you haven't heard
of Mechanical Turk before,

00:17:49.760 --> 00:17:54.760
it's a platform that is used
to get large amounts of people

00:17:54.940 --> 00:17:58.730
to do small tasks for you
for small amounts of money.

00:17:58.730 --> 00:18:00.560
It's used a lot of times by researchers

00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:02.580
and it's used among others,

00:18:02.580 --> 00:18:06.600
and it's used for things that
humans are pretty good at,

00:18:06.600 --> 00:18:08.060
but computers are not so good at,

00:18:08.060 --> 00:18:10.740
so looking at an image and tagging it

00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:12.750
or transcribing some audio.

00:18:12.750 --> 00:18:14.157
I'll just play this first video.

00:18:14.157 --> 00:18:19.157
(engine revving)
(heels clicking)

00:18:21.788 --> 00:18:24.705
(electronic music)

00:18:25.755 --> 00:18:29.700
So I took this Amazon
Mechanical Turk service,

00:18:29.700 --> 00:18:31.410
and I attached it to my dating life,

00:18:31.410 --> 00:18:34.060
and I went on a series
of dates with people

00:18:34.060 --> 00:18:35.590
that I met on OkCupid,

00:18:35.590 --> 00:18:39.030
and I paid the Turk worker
here just to watch the stream,

00:18:39.030 --> 00:18:41.000
decide what I should do or say next,

00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:43.593
and send it to me, and I'd
get it via text message.

00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:47.830
I had to perform these
messages immediately.

00:18:47.830 --> 00:18:49.630
I kind of experimented with the interface

00:18:49.630 --> 00:18:51.790
to figure out the best
way to get the feedback

00:18:51.790 --> 00:18:53.420
from these people.

00:18:53.420 --> 00:18:55.350
These are some of the things they said.

00:19:31.200 --> 00:19:32.700
So one of the most surprising

00:19:34.682 --> 00:19:36.258
things I found when I did this

00:19:36.258 --> 00:19:39.490
was once I kind of gave into
the system of hyper-control,

00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:40.800
I actually found some freedom.

00:19:40.800 --> 00:19:44.260
I found this freedom from me,

00:19:44.260 --> 00:19:45.990
from the limits and ideas I had

00:19:45.990 --> 00:19:47.490
about the sorts of things I did

00:19:47.490 --> 00:19:48.920
and the sorts of things I might say,

00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:51.079
because I had to go beyond them.

00:19:51.079 --> 00:19:53.750
Then I did this for a month
and sometime afterwards

00:19:53.750 --> 00:19:55.670
I found myself on a date unassisted,

00:19:55.670 --> 00:19:58.760
and my date asked me if he could kiss me,

00:19:58.760 --> 00:20:02.010
and I realized I didn't
have any basis anymore

00:20:02.010 --> 00:20:03.553
for making that decision.

00:20:03.553 --> 00:20:05.860
(audience laughs)

00:20:05.860 --> 00:20:06.900
Strangely, during the whole thing

00:20:06.900 --> 00:20:09.800
I felt a sense of closeness
with those that were watching.

00:20:09.800 --> 00:20:11.070
I felt like like they would protect me

00:20:11.070 --> 00:20:12.680
even though I was totally
aware that they actually

00:20:12.680 --> 00:20:14.000
wouldn't do anything probably

00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:15.950
if I was thrown in the back of a truck,

00:20:16.910 --> 00:20:18.930
and I wonder how do we
feel when a surveillant

00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:21.480
omniscient gaze is watching?

00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:24.103
And how do we feel when we
think that it's one of care?

00:20:26.190 --> 00:20:28.310
So that led me to this next project.

00:20:28.310 --> 00:20:30.310
Again, I'll just play the trailer for it.

00:20:30.310 --> 00:20:33.227
