So this was a trailer for a performance,

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:51.900
and it was a trailer for
this service called Follower.

00:21:51.900 --> 00:21:53.860
To get Follower, you go to a website,

00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:54.860
and you'd sign up.

00:21:54.860 --> 00:21:56.050
You'd answer two questions:

00:21:56.050 --> 00:21:57.230
Why do you want to be followed?

00:21:57.230 --> 00:21:58.880
And why should someone follow me?

00:22:00.160 --> 00:22:01.047
People would say things like,

00:22:01.047 --> 00:22:03.027
"I believe my life has more
of an online importance

00:22:03.027 --> 00:22:04.597
"than it does in real life,

00:22:04.597 --> 00:22:06.667
"and I would like some
clarification that my life

00:22:06.667 --> 00:22:09.360
"in the real world
means more than online."

00:22:09.360 --> 00:22:11.367
Or, "I live a cloistered life
in my apartment and office,

00:22:11.367 --> 00:22:12.687
"and when I walk into the world

00:22:12.687 --> 00:22:14.187
"I feel completely covered in eyes,

00:22:14.187 --> 00:22:15.837
"as if everyone was looking at me.

00:22:15.837 --> 00:22:19.141
"I know they aren't, but I
want to know at least one is."

00:22:19.141 --> 00:22:21.190
So if you're selected, you're sent a link,

00:22:21.190 --> 00:22:22.023
and you download an app,

00:22:22.023 --> 00:22:23.953
and it just is waiting for a follower.

00:22:25.110 --> 00:22:26.040
Then one day you wake up,

00:22:26.040 --> 00:22:26.940
you don't know when it will happen,

00:22:26.940 --> 00:22:29.700
but you're notified your
follower is now following you.

00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:33.510
It starts broadcasting your
GPS location to your follower,

00:22:33.510 --> 00:22:34.920
and the follower was me.

00:22:34.920 --> 00:22:36.590
So I was the blue dot
running down the street

00:22:36.590 --> 00:22:37.970
after the red marker,

00:22:37.970 --> 00:22:40.990
and I would use this mix of
GPS and just visual contact

00:22:40.990 --> 00:22:43.800
to try to keep close to them all day long.

00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:44.770
At the end of the day,

00:22:44.770 --> 00:22:46.310
they would get one photo of themselves

00:22:46.310 --> 00:22:48.260
taken somewhere during the day,

00:22:48.260 --> 00:22:50.927
and the notification, "You're
no longer being followed."

00:22:52.190 --> 00:22:53.320
So these are some of the photos.

00:22:53.320 --> 00:22:55.730
The titles are taken from those questions:

00:22:55.730 --> 00:22:57.260
Why do you want to be followed?

00:22:57.260 --> 00:22:58.910
Or why should someone follow you?

00:23:05.640 --> 00:23:06.610
- [Woman] Can you read the title?

00:23:06.610 --> 00:23:08.903
- Oh sorry, yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:13.053
I've always wanted a non-violent stalker.

00:23:14.210 --> 00:23:16.313
I want to be seen just for one day.

00:23:17.810 --> 00:23:19.813
I want to be both alone and not.

00:23:21.180 --> 00:23:23.660
I'm obsessed with the difference
between how I see myself

00:23:23.660 --> 00:23:25.053
and how the world sees me.

00:23:26.300 --> 00:23:27.313
Because I'm lonely.

00:23:29.270 --> 00:23:31.170
So we're living in this weird anxious time

00:23:31.170 --> 00:23:32.680
where on one hand it
feels like surveillance

00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:33.936
is pervasive and out of control,

00:23:33.936 --> 00:23:36.500
and on the other hand we
have this intense desire

00:23:36.500 --> 00:23:39.560
to be seen, to be heard,
to be followed and liked,

00:23:39.560 --> 00:23:41.840
and to share every intimate
details of our lives.

00:23:41.840 --> 00:23:43.977
There are sites you can
go to to buy followers;

00:23:43.977 --> 00:23:45.910
$10 will get you 1,000.

00:23:45.910 --> 00:23:48.160
You can find out how
real your followers are.

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:50.490
But is that desire to
be seen really fulfilled

00:23:50.490 --> 00:23:53.520
by watching a follower count tick upwards?

00:23:53.520 --> 00:23:55.220
Or is there something more fulfilling

00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:58.770
about having a real-life person out there?

00:23:58.770 --> 00:23:59.810
How does it change?

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:02.950
How do we behave when we know
or think someone's watching?

00:24:02.950 --> 00:24:06.030
And does it change when we're
talking about one person

00:24:06.030 --> 00:24:08.250
in physical life versus a crowd

00:24:08.250 --> 00:24:10.000
of attention-divided people online?

00:24:11.360 --> 00:24:14.882
Then Follower offers surveillance
as a luxury experience.

00:24:14.882 --> 00:24:16.970
This is an app for
people that not only have

00:24:16.970 --> 00:24:19.190
nothing to hide, but need to be seen.

00:24:19.190 --> 00:24:21.540
Embedded in this offer is a question

00:24:21.540 --> 00:24:23.410
of who wouldn't want this app?

00:24:23.410 --> 00:24:26.050
Who doesn't have that privilege of hiding

00:24:26.050 --> 00:24:27.720
just because of who they
are or what they look like

00:24:27.720 --> 00:24:28.770
or what they believe?

00:24:30.010 --> 00:24:34.470
And then...
(audience laughs)

00:24:34.470 --> 00:24:38.950
Yeah, so a few years ago with
Edward Snowden and the NSA,

00:24:38.950 --> 00:24:42.260
surveillance becomes this
political issue again,

00:24:42.260 --> 00:24:43.640
but maybe the white man is the only one

00:24:43.640 --> 00:24:46.200
that found this sense of
being watched unfamiliar,

00:24:46.200 --> 00:24:47.600
because I think plenty of us are used to

00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:50.830
watching over our shoulders
and reading between the lines

00:24:50.830 --> 00:24:53.500
and feeling the ways we're
measured, tracked and shaped

00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:55.340
by implicit power systems.

00:24:55.340 --> 00:24:57.477
He says, "Just some woman laughing,

00:24:57.477 --> 00:24:59.790
"glossing over the implication."

00:24:59.790 --> 00:25:03.827
The opposite, a woman following, sorry...

00:25:03.827 --> 00:25:05.707
"The opposite, a man following a woman

00:25:05.707 --> 00:25:08.057
"would be terrifying and happens.

00:25:08.057 --> 00:25:10.299
"And I wondered, I don't
think I've ever seen the words

00:25:10.299 --> 00:25:12.717
"just some man in any headline every."

00:25:14.990 --> 00:25:17.100
Then it seems like we're
willing to try any app

00:25:17.100 --> 00:25:20.410
that promises us something
new or novel or convenient.

00:25:20.410 --> 00:25:22.823
I really like this
hashtag, #lifeafterchores.

00:25:22.823 --> 00:25:24.270
The chores disappeared.

00:25:24.270 --> 00:25:26.380
But the chores didn't disappear,
just the people doing them,

00:25:26.380 --> 00:25:27.660
because we don't have to see them anymore;

00:25:27.660 --> 00:25:28.990
we just push a button on our app,

00:25:28.990 --> 00:25:31.541
and they can show up when we're gone.

00:25:31.541 --> 00:25:33.360
For instance, sit on a beach

00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:35.960
and hold a reserved fire
pit for you all day,

00:25:35.960 --> 00:25:38.140
or kill a bug in your apartment.

00:25:38.140 --> 00:25:39.690
Then with apps like Uber or TaskRabbit,

00:25:39.690 --> 00:25:41.870
you push a button, and you
watch as the person you summon

00:25:41.870 --> 00:25:43.830
comes to you on a map.

00:25:43.830 --> 00:25:46.120
I wanted to invert that, so with Follower

00:25:46.120 --> 00:25:48.360
they don't track me on
a map, I track them.

00:25:48.360 --> 00:25:50.090
What they get instead is just the thought

00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:51.690
that there's a person out there.

00:25:55.570 --> 00:25:56.800
Follower was in public,

00:25:56.800 --> 00:25:59.357
a space we already have
kind of limited privacy,

00:25:59.357 --> 00:26:02.250
but how does that translate to the home?

00:26:02.250 --> 00:26:03.600
I started talking to a lot of people

00:26:03.600 --> 00:26:04.700
about their feelings about home,

00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:05.757
and everybody kept saying,

00:26:05.757 --> 00:26:08.750
"It's the place where I get
to be myself, the real me,"

00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:10.871
and probably you feel similar.

00:26:10.871 --> 00:26:13.410
Meanwhile, we're being
sold these smart devices

00:26:13.410 --> 00:26:15.280
that outfit our homes
with surveillance cameras,

00:26:15.280 --> 00:26:17.190
sensors and automated control,

00:26:17.190 --> 00:26:21.060
offering us convenience at
the cost of loss of privacy

00:26:21.060 --> 00:26:23.500
and control over our lives and homes.

00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:25.870
We're meant to think these
slick, plastic pieces

00:26:25.870 --> 00:26:27.690
of technology are about utility,

00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:29.590
but the space they invade is personal.

