01:04:04.532 --> 01:04:05.753
Seanna, you were leaning in.

01:04:06.590 --> 01:04:09.673
- I have a specific set
of questions for Lauren.

01:04:12.108 --> 01:04:17.108
I was thinking, one way to
interpret your work is that it's,

01:04:17.710 --> 01:04:21.010
for me, it kind of shows
some of the difference

01:04:21.010 --> 01:04:24.010
between creativity and
freedom, 'cause it's

01:04:24.010 --> 01:04:29.010
such a remarkably creative set
of interventions and ideas,

01:04:29.780 --> 01:04:32.170
but I was wondering,
from your perspective,

01:04:32.170 --> 01:04:36.100
while you were following
people or while you were

01:04:36.100 --> 01:04:39.963
assisting them in Get
Lauren, did you feel free?

01:04:41.480 --> 01:04:44.430
And how did you help your subjects

01:04:44.430 --> 01:04:47.490
to retain or regain their independence

01:04:47.490 --> 01:04:51.763
after this kind of hierarchical
relationship with you?

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:56.850
- I think was made those performances work

01:04:56.850 --> 01:04:59.410
was that it was actually more complicated

01:04:59.410 --> 01:05:02.990
than just me having control,
because on one hand,

01:05:02.990 --> 01:05:05.060
yes I see them and they don't see me,

01:05:05.060 --> 01:05:08.240
or I'm controlling everything
and I can do whatever I want,

01:05:08.240 --> 01:05:10.210
but on the other hand,
and maybe because of

01:05:10.210 --> 01:05:12.170
the role I chose to
take in the performance,

01:05:12.170 --> 01:05:14.860
I'm tethered to them so
they move wherever they want

01:05:14.860 --> 01:05:17.710
and I have to run after them
and try to catch that bus

01:05:17.710 --> 01:05:20.740
or, you know, they're just
sitting there and watching TV

01:05:20.740 --> 01:05:22.500
and every once in a while, might ask me to

01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:24.730
make them some popcorn,
and I'm sitting on the edge

01:05:24.730 --> 01:05:27.130
of my seat, waiting for the
next thing they might want

01:05:27.130 --> 01:05:29.100
and maybe there's an
eight-hour time difference

01:05:29.100 --> 01:05:30.230
'cause they're in another country

01:05:30.230 --> 01:05:35.230
and I'm up at 4 AM, so I think that,

01:05:35.750 --> 01:05:40.040
that relationship of us both
having some amount of control

01:05:40.040 --> 01:05:44.958
and some amount of lack
of it, bound us together

01:05:44.958 --> 01:05:48.470
and made it more complicated than just

01:05:48.470 --> 01:05:50.573
one person watching another.

01:05:52.170 --> 01:05:55.290
And I think maybe that's trying to get at

01:05:55.290 --> 01:05:57.743
some of these systems of
control and surveillance

01:05:57.743 --> 01:06:01.590
that we're within, yeah,
so maybe Google's watching

01:06:01.590 --> 01:06:04.090
or the government or whoever,
but even those networks

01:06:04.090 --> 01:06:09.090
are so complicated that it's
not, it's not so simple.

01:06:09.220 --> 01:06:13.040
The structures that are put in
places, who holds the power,

01:06:13.040 --> 01:06:15.940
and I think I tried to start to pull apart

01:06:15.940 --> 01:06:18.090
that messiness and understand.

01:06:18.090 --> 01:06:20.060
- [Seanna] But would you
end up agreeing with me

01:06:20.060 --> 01:06:23.380
or resisting that, your
work kind of shows that

01:06:24.790 --> 01:06:27.250
innovation and freedom are not identical?

01:06:27.250 --> 01:06:30.183
It's highly innovative, highly
innovative relationships,

01:06:31.859 --> 01:06:34.840
not free on either end,
and that you can be

01:06:34.840 --> 01:06:37.210
on the bottom of a power
relationship or on the top

01:06:37.210 --> 01:06:40.230
of a power relationship
and neither can be free.

01:06:40.230 --> 01:06:42.360
'Cause some of what you
said just suggests thaT,

01:06:42.360 --> 01:06:44.430
I'm wondering if you agree.

01:06:44.430 --> 01:06:46.830
- Yeah, I would agree, and
